# Production builds: full site by default. Set to "instalatori" for event-only mode (Instalatori page only).
# Local `npm run dev` is always full site.
# VITE_SITE_MODE=instalatori

# Optional: API base URL (production/staging). Dev uses proxy /api or localhost.
# VITE_API_URL=https://your-api.vercel.app

# Google Sign-In (GIS/FedCM). Must match GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID configured on the API.
#
# Vercel: Settings → Environment Variables → add VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID for Production
# and Preview (and Development if you use `vercel dev`). Redeploy after saving — Vite
# inlines these at build time; without them the login page shows “lipsește în frontend”.
#
# Dacă pe Vercel vezi „Token Google invalid” / 401: de obicei VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID ≠
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID pe Railway, sau lipsește originea Vercel în Google Cloud:
#   • Același string de client ID (Web) în Vercel și în Railway (fără spații, același proiect GCP).
#   • Google Cloud → Credentials → OAuth 2.0 Client ID → Authorized JavaScript origins:
#       https://<proiect>.vercel.app  și  https://baterino.ro  (fără / la final).
#   • Preview deployments: fie adaugi fiecare URL preview, fie testezi doar pe Production.
#
# Local dev: In Google Cloud Console → Credentials → your OAuth 2.0 Web client →
# “Authorized JavaScript origins”, add BOTH (exact URL, no trailing slash):
#   http://localhost:5173
#   http://127.0.0.1:5173
# Otherwise GIS shows: unregistered_origin. If Vite prints another port (e.g. 5174), add that
# origin too. If you open dev via LAN (http://192.168.x.x:5173), add that exact origin too, or
# use http://localhost:5173. FedCM is off in `vite` dev and on localhost/private IPs so GIS uses
# the classic prompt locally (matches production behavior on Vercel).
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=138491232272-dnrcb5thtn8d8cq484vqf4pl5tkva5i2.apps.googleusercontent.com

# Google Maps Locator Plus on /contact (Maps JavaScript API).
# Create/restrict the key in Google Cloud Console (HTTP referrer: baterino.ro, localhost, Vercel previews).
# VITE_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=your-maps-javascript-api-key
# Optional Map ID from Cloud Console → Map Management (defaults to Google's DEMO_MAP_ID for dev).
# VITE_GOOGLE_MAP_ID=DEMO_MAP_ID
